## ğŸ¨ Color Palette

### Primary Reds
- `--theme-red-vivid`: #E50000 (Primary accent)
- `--theme-red-bright`: #FF0000 (Hover states)
- `--theme-red-dim`: #CC0000 (Emphasis)
- `--theme-red-dark`: #B30000 (Active states)

### Greyscale
- `--theme-grey-bright`: #E0E0E0 (High-emphasis text)
- `--theme-grey-medium`: #A3A3A3 (Medium-emphasis text)
- `--theme-grey-dark`: #7A7A7A (Low-emphasis text)
- `--theme-grey-darker`: #5A5A5A (Disabled states)

### Blacks
- `--theme-black-deep`: #0A0A0A (Depth effects, code blocks)
- `--theme-black-base`: #121212 (Primary background)
- `--theme-black-raised`: #1E1E1E (Cards, raised surfaces)
- `--theme-black-surface`: #252525 (High surfaces)
- `--theme-black-ui`: #181818 (UI frames)
- `--theme-black-border`: #2A2A2A (Borders)

## ğŸ”§ Customization

All colors use CSS variables. To customize:

1. Open `theme.css`
2. Find the variable you want to change
3. Modify the hex value
4. Reload Obsidian (Ctrl+R or Cmd+R)

Example:
```css
/* Change primary accent from red to blue */
--theme-red-vivid: #0000E5;
```

